The paper discusses the comparative study of state-of-the-art approaches for question classification task using pre-trained word embeddings and human-labeled data. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers NLP and ML. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as it covers various ML techniques. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) covers NLP and ML as well and is therefore another likely category. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as it covers the task of classifying questions. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as it covers the use of neural networks in ML.
